<paragraph id="8BA33061FFB06C60FF6240FEA45DF928" blockId="6.[130,775,1459,1779]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313">
Based on our material, we show that the subsutural flexures are variable from shallow (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB06C60FE2440DEA75AF9E8" authority="(Hoernes &amp; Auinger, 1879))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Hoernes &amp; Auinger" baseAuthorityYear="1879" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conilithes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brezinae">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB06C60FE2440DEA4F1F9C8" box="[450,642,1529,1555]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313">Conilithes brezinae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFB06C60FD7640DEA764F9E8" author="HOERNES R. &amp; AUINGER M." pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" pagination="1 - 52" refId="ref19161" refString="HOERNES R. &amp; AUINGER M. 1879. - Die Gasteropoden der Meeres- Ablagerungen der ersten und zweiten Miocanen Mediterran-Stufe in der Osterreichisch-Ungarischen Monarchie. Abhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koniglichen Geologischen Reichsanstalt 12: 1 - 52." type="journal article" year="1879">Hoernes &amp; Auinger, 1879</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
to deep (e.g., mean SSFD of 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB06C60FDB6433EA576F9E8" authority="Psarras &amp; Koskeridou &amp; Merle, 2021" authorityName="Psarras &amp; Koskeridou &amp; Merle" authorityYear="2021" box="[592,773,1561,1587]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conilithes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="herodus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB06C60FDB6433EA576F9E8" box="[592,773,1561,1587]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313">Conilithes herodus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25B5108FFB06C60FF62431EA6B3F988" box="[132,192,1593,1619]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). In addition, early teleoconchs whorls can be devoid of beads (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB06C60FEE1437FA4E0F9A8" authority="(Brocchi, 1814))" authorityName="" baseAuthorityName="Brocchi" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[263,659,1624,1651]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conilithes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="striatulus">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB06C60FEE1437FA7A6F9A9" box="[263,469,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313">Conilithes striatulus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFB06C60FE02437FA4F2F9A8" author="BROCCHI G." box="[484,641,1624,1651]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" pagination="1 - 2" refId="ref17383" refString="BROCCHI G. 1814. - Conchiologia fossile subapennina, con osservazioni geologiche sugli Apennini e sul suolo adiacente. Stamperia Reale, Milano, 1 - 2, 712 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 11569" type="book chapter" year="1814">Brocchi, 1814</bibRefCitation>
))
</taxonomicName>
and rarely species display beads on their last whorls (e.g., 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4BE2FFB06C60FD8C435FA489F948" box="[618,762,1656,1683]" class="Gastropoda" family="Conidae" genus="Conilithes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B968EC73FFB06C60FD8C435FA4A1F949" box="[618,722,1656,1682]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313">Conilithes</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
). The stratigraphical range of the genus is Eocene to Pliocene of Europe (Proto-Mediterranean and Paratethys) and North America (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4D90FFB06C60FF0843FFA46DF929" author="HARZHAUSER M. &amp; LANDAU B." box="[238,542,1752,1778]" pageId="6" pageNumber="1313" pagination="1" refId="ref18832" refString="HARZHAUSER M. &amp; LANDAU B. 2016. - A revision of the Neogene Conidae and Conorbidae (Gastropoda) of the Paratethys Sea. Zootaxa 4210 (1): 001 - 178. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4210.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Harzhauser &amp; Landau 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
